<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-63527" src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/apc2.jpg" alt="" width="596" height="402" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/apc2.jpg 596w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/apc2-150x101.jpg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/apc2-420x283.jpg 420w" sizes="(max-width: 596px) 100vw, 596px" /> The All Progressives Congress (APC) Appeal Committee for Saturday State Congress in Adamawa has commenced sitting in Yola. Speaking to newsmen Tuesday in Yola, Chairman of the committee, Dr. Musa Gwarzo, said the committee would sit for only one day (Tuesday). “We are here to hear from all those who have grievances over the State Congress. They are free to bring it written or verbal. “We are going to assess such complaints and make our judgments, ” Gwarzo said. He said he was impressed with the development that had taken place in Adamawa, and lauded the APC-led administration in the state for making the party proud. (NAN) Hinatufe Henry Solomon is a graduate of Computer Science, specialist in ICT Support Services. Henry is also proficient in use of most online journalism tools and Social media management. He currently serve as Information Technology Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network.